ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Average of the last 30 seconds of the recording , microsiemens
The peak value of the interview recording, microsiemens
Time in seconds, since start of interview recording, when peak happened
The average of the first 30 seconds of last minute of the recording, microsiemens
Edesense_max - edesense_base (Max ('Interview' reading) - Average(last 30 seconds of 'Base')), microsiemens
Edesense_max - edesense_start (Max ('Interview' reading) - Average(first 30 seconds of 'Interview')), microsiemens
Edesense_max - edesense_end (Max ('Interview' reading) - Average(first 30 seconds of  last minute of 'Interview')), microsiemens
Edesense_start - edesense_end (Average (first 30 seconds of 'Interview') - Average(first 30 seconds of  last minute of 'Interview')), microsiemens
